WEBVTT

00:00.081 --> 00:02.905
I want to come home.
But it's not Jon's baby.

00:02.905 --> 00:06.043
Katherine:
<i>It's crazy how one decision</i>
<i>can change your life forever.</i>

00:06.043 --> 00:08.476
Eddie: My daughter
comes home today.

00:08.476 --> 00:10.728
I can't even
call her my daughter.

00:10.728 --> 00:13.314
It's okay, Mom.
Our dad's not here.

00:13.314 --> 00:15.524
<i>All the plans you made</i>
<i>slip away.</i>

00:15.524 --> 00:18.027
This is the car people get
when they're having kids.

00:18.027 --> 00:19.653
I think
we should get it.

00:19.653 --> 00:21.322
<i>So you accept a new reality.</i>

00:21.322 --> 00:22.865
I'm directing
this commercial.

00:22.865 --> 00:25.701
No, you hate
directing commercials.
No. Let me help you, baby.

00:25.701 --> 00:27.244
<i>Sometimes that's a good thing.</i>

00:27.244 --> 00:28.662
Maggie,
you're in remission.

00:28.662 --> 00:30.414
Oh, thank God.
[ Laughs ]

00:30.414 --> 00:31.624
<i>Other times...</i>

00:31.624 --> 00:32.917
About the night
Chad died.

00:32.917 --> 00:34.210
Eric has
your brother's heart.

00:34.210 --> 00:35.544
<i>...it's more of a shock.</i>

00:35.544 --> 00:37.546
Get in!
It's pouring.

00:37.546 --> 00:39.590
<i>And how do you</i>
<i>figure out your future</i>

00:39.590 --> 00:41.467
<i>when you can't</i>
<i>forget your past?</i>

00:41.467 --> 00:44.011
Maybe instead of trying
to get back to what we were,

00:44.011 --> 00:45.888
we figure out
what we're gonna be.

00:48.641 --> 00:50.768
Katherine: Oh, cool.
Check this out.

00:50.768 --> 00:52.561
It says here
that a black hole

00:52.561 --> 00:54.980
can be billions of times
bigger than the sun.

00:54.980 --> 00:56.982
Hey. Guess what.

00:56.982 --> 00:58.901
They finally finished
the house across the street.

00:58.901 --> 01:01.445
Yeah, there's an open house
tomorrow from 2:00 to 4:00.

01:03.197 --> 01:06.200
That real‐estate lady from
the bus stop bench came by.

01:06.200 --> 01:07.993
You're not
gonna believe it.

01:07.993 --> 01:10.287
Her teeth really <i>are</i>
that white.

01:10.287 --> 01:11.413
[ Both laugh ]

01:11.413 --> 01:12.873
Oh, read the section
on dinosaurs.

01:12.873 --> 01:14.500
Okay.

01:16.418 --> 01:17.545
Oh, here we go.

01:17.545 --> 01:19.255
What the hell is this?

01:19.255 --> 01:20.881
T!
Theo.

01:20.881 --> 01:24.802
I'm sorry, but what do these two
think they're doing?

01:24.802 --> 01:28.055
The woolly mammoth is giving its
friend the pterodactyl a ride.

01:28.055 --> 01:29.306
It's...cute.

01:29.306 --> 01:30.975
Cute?!

01:30.975 --> 01:33.018
Everybody knows
woolly mammoths and dinosaurs

01:33.018 --> 01:35.229
didn't exist
at the same time.

01:35.229 --> 01:36.605
Don't look at me.

01:36.605 --> 01:38.899
My only reference
is "The Flintstones."

01:38.899 --> 01:40.359
Look it up.

01:40.359 --> 01:42.069
My iPad's
right over there.

01:42.069 --> 01:44.280
It's a commonly known fact,

01:44.280 --> 01:48.075
like koala bears and humans
have the same fingerprints.

01:48.075 --> 01:50.244
RRRRRight.

01:50.244 --> 01:52.162
Mom knows
what I'm talking about.

01:52.162 --> 01:54.248
Apparently,
koala fingerprints

01:54.248 --> 01:56.750
are so indistinguishable
from humans

01:56.750 --> 01:59.420
that sometimes they get confused
at crime scenes.

01:59.420 --> 02:03.215
They can't even tell them apart
even under a microscope.

02:03.215 --> 02:05.217
Huh?

02:05.217 --> 02:06.468
Dad, what'd you find?

02:07.803 --> 02:08.596
Um...

02:11.891 --> 02:13.601
Yeah, looks like
you were right, bud.

02:13.601 --> 02:16.729
Dinosaurs died 60 million years
before woolly mammoths.

02:16.729 --> 02:19.481
See? This book
is full of lies.

02:19.481 --> 02:21.567
I don't know
what to believe anymore.

02:22.818 --> 02:24.820
Yeah, me neither.

02:30.743 --> 02:31.785
Uh‐oh.

02:31.785 --> 02:33.537
Hey!

02:33.537 --> 02:36.123
Hey, the floss is stuck
in my teeth!

02:36.123 --> 02:37.958
How do I get that out?

02:37.958 --> 02:39.543
Ow!

02:39.543 --> 02:41.420
[ Groans ]

02:41.420 --> 02:42.796
Cancel everything!

02:42.796 --> 02:44.423
I need you to cancel
the whole day!

02:45.424 --> 02:47.343
Ohh!

02:47.343 --> 02:48.552
Mayday!
[ Sighs ]

02:50.137 --> 02:52.890
Oh, this is unpleasant.

02:52.890 --> 02:54.600
Ow!

02:54.600 --> 02:56.894
Got it! All clear!

02:56.894 --> 02:58.854
Man, that was a ride, huh?

02:58.854 --> 03:01.649
And <i>that</i> is why
I do not floss.

03:01.649 --> 03:07.863
♪♪

03:07.863 --> 03:14.036
♪♪

03:14.036 --> 03:15.162
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

03:15.162 --> 03:16.956
Gary: Aww!

03:16.956 --> 03:18.540
I just got a text
from Gail.

03:18.540 --> 03:22.753
Everyone in our remission group
is very excited to see us today.

03:22.753 --> 03:24.421
You know, I'm just gonna
put myself out there

03:24.421 --> 03:25.923
and say that after
the last couple weeks,

03:25.923 --> 03:27.341
I think it'd be
a very good idea

03:27.341 --> 03:29.051
for us to spend
a little quality time together.

03:29.051 --> 03:31.303
Oh, my God!
Oh...my...God!

03:31.303 --> 03:32.972
It is a good thing
that I just peed.

03:32.972 --> 03:35.391
[ Exhales heavily ]
You scared the crap out of me.

03:35.391 --> 03:36.850
What are you doing?

03:36.850 --> 03:37.768
Looking for
my other sneaker.

03:37.768 --> 03:38.978
I'm trying
to get a run in

03:38.978 --> 03:41.021
before I meet D
at my old apartment.

03:41.021 --> 03:43.983
Oh, I...thought we were supposed
to visit our support group.

03:43.983 --> 03:46.068
There hasn't been a line
at the doughnut table

03:46.068 --> 03:48.404
since I floated the theory
that crullers cause cancer.

03:48.404 --> 03:50.447
Awww. That's today.

03:50.447 --> 03:51.740
I can't.

03:51.740 --> 03:53.200
I promised D
I would meet her

03:53.200 --> 03:55.786
so we could stage the apartment
to post photos.

03:55.786 --> 03:57.621
We really need to find
a subletter.

03:57.621 --> 03:59.331
I'm sorry.
Are you mad?

03:59.331 --> 04:00.791
At you?
Mm.

04:00.791 --> 04:02.751
For fully moving in
with me?

04:02.751 --> 04:05.212
And paying half my rent
and utilities?

04:05.212 --> 04:07.047
By the way,
you still owe me for April.

04:07.047 --> 04:08.424
[ Chuckles ]

04:08.424 --> 04:09.800
We can go next week.

04:09.800 --> 04:10.884
[ Colin grunts ]

04:10.884 --> 04:13.053
Colin!
Oh, my God!

04:13.053 --> 04:14.221
Oh, dude, come on!

04:14.221 --> 04:16.807
You have
two perfectly good ‐‐

04:16.807 --> 04:19.184
Oh, he's been
licking those, too.

04:19.184 --> 04:21.603
You, sir, have had
a busy morning.

04:21.603 --> 04:24.565
[ Charlie fussing ]
Delilah: Okay, Charlie,
this is one, and this is two.

04:24.565 --> 04:25.899
Danny: I call first ball.
And again, one...

04:25.899 --> 04:26.942
Sophie:
Yeah. No. I'm older.

04:26.942 --> 04:28.861
...and two.

04:28.861 --> 04:30.654
Hey, Mom.
Mm‐hmm?

04:30.654 --> 04:34.533
You do realize you uploaded
the same photo twice, right?

04:34.533 --> 04:35.993
[ Key clacks ]
I do now.

04:35.993 --> 04:37.494
[ Laughs ]

04:37.494 --> 04:39.830
Hey, you guys, before you go,
what do you think

04:39.830 --> 04:42.291
about using this for
Charlie's birth announcement?

04:42.291 --> 04:43.751
Wait. We're not doing a photo
of the whole family?

04:43.751 --> 04:45.669
Well, I was thinking
maybe ‐‐

04:45.669 --> 04:47.129
maybe it could
just be Charlie.

04:47.129 --> 04:49.506
But my birth announcement
had you and Dad.

04:49.506 --> 04:51.133
And Danny's had
all three of us.

04:52.426 --> 04:53.886
Why should this
be any different?

04:53.886 --> 04:55.971
Uh, because
Dad's not here?

04:55.971 --> 04:57.723
Uh, yeah,
I know Dad's not here,

04:57.723 --> 04:59.850
but Charlie still has
a family.

04:59.850 --> 05:01.769
She has <i>us.</i>

05:01.769 --> 05:04.104
It's tradition, so...

05:04.104 --> 05:05.606
Yeah.
No, you're right.

05:05.606 --> 05:07.483
You're right.
I'll call the photographer.

05:07.483 --> 05:09.068
Great.

05:09.068 --> 05:10.444
You're gonna love it.

05:10.444 --> 05:12.404
And you're going down.

05:12.404 --> 05:14.114
Danny: Yeah, well,
of course I'm going down.

05:14.114 --> 05:15.532
You're like
6 feet tall.

05:15.532 --> 05:17.076
[ Door opens ]

05:17.076 --> 05:18.911
Wait. You're talking to <i>me,</i>
not to the car, right?

05:18.911 --> 05:19.870
[ Laughs ]

05:19.870 --> 05:21.330
And cut!

05:21.330 --> 05:22.831
Love it. Perfect.

05:22.831 --> 05:24.458
[ Bell rings ]
But let's do it again.

05:24.458 --> 05:26.085
Hey, babe.
Just brought you some coffee.

05:26.085 --> 05:27.461
Oh, that's sweet,

05:27.461 --> 05:29.588
but you know that we have coffee
at craft services, right?

05:29.588 --> 05:30.839
That's where I got it.

05:30.839 --> 05:31.924
[ Both laugh ]

05:31.924 --> 05:33.509
But they don't
have this.
Mmm.

05:33.509 --> 05:34.968
I'll be back for more of that
in a second.

05:34.968 --> 05:36.136
Yeah, yeah.

05:36.136 --> 05:37.805
And this is for you.
Thank you.

05:37.805 --> 05:39.056
Nate, quick note
for this next take.

05:39.056 --> 05:40.265
Hey, Don. Hey, Gene.
Hey.

05:40.265 --> 05:41.517
How's it going?

05:41.517 --> 05:42.518
Well, uh,
actually, it's ‐‐

05:42.518 --> 05:43.644
It's great.

05:43.644 --> 05:45.187
Fantastic is
what it is.

05:45.187 --> 05:46.605
Your man is incredible.

05:46.605 --> 05:48.941
He came in and put a whole new
spin on the campaign.

05:48.941 --> 05:51.402
All him.
Honestly, it was all him.

05:51.402 --> 05:53.320
And...us, as well.

05:53.320 --> 05:54.822
Group effort.

05:54.822 --> 05:57.950
I hear you're hosting
a big anniversary lunch today.

05:57.950 --> 05:59.868
Mm‐hmm. Rome's folks
are married 50 years today.

05:59.868 --> 06:01.161
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

06:01.161 --> 06:03.122
I've actually been married
<i>30</i> years.

06:03.122 --> 06:04.123
Not in a row.

06:04.123 --> 06:05.457
Oh, sorry.

06:05.457 --> 06:07.000
My dad's gonna be looking
for a new wife

06:07.000 --> 06:08.627
if he didn't get my mom that
cruise she's been asking for.

06:08.627 --> 06:10.963
[ Laughs ]
Oh, he got her that cruise.

06:10.963 --> 06:12.798
Right?
Of course
he got her the cruise.

06:12.798 --> 06:13.966
He'd be an idiot
not to ‐‐

06:15.592 --> 06:17.386
Maybe give him a call.
[ Laughs ]

06:17.386 --> 06:18.345
We're all set.
Thanks.

06:18.345 --> 06:19.805
Hey, Nate!

06:19.805 --> 06:22.433
Remember,
she's your wife, okay?

06:22.433 --> 06:23.600
So it should be hard
to tell her.

06:23.600 --> 06:24.893
This way,
when she's on board,

06:24.893 --> 06:26.228
it'll be
that much more rewarding.

06:26.228 --> 06:28.021
Got it.
Alright.

06:28.021 --> 06:30.732
And...action!

06:30.732 --> 06:33.527
Babe [Chuckles]
the RX is great.

06:33.527 --> 06:35.404
But it's just
the two of us.

06:35.404 --> 06:36.947
Well...

06:36.947 --> 06:38.866
what if it <i>weren't</i>
just the two of us?

06:38.866 --> 06:40.325
♪♪

06:40.325 --> 06:42.494
Are you saying
what I <i>think</i> you're saying?

06:42.494 --> 06:45.122
That's <i>exactly</i>
what I'm saying.

06:45.122 --> 06:46.957
I love you.

06:46.957 --> 06:49.710
Wait. You're talking to <i>me,</i>
not to the car, right?

06:49.710 --> 06:52.045
[ Laughing ]
And cut!

06:52.045 --> 06:54.173
[ Bell rings ]
That is amazing!

06:54.173 --> 06:55.174
Don: I told you.
I told you.

06:55.174 --> 06:56.884
Give me a second.

06:56.884 --> 06:58.594
Man: Okay, everybody,
take five.
Rome is the best.

06:58.594 --> 07:00.721
No, Nate, <i>we</i> are the best,
because...
[ Headphones thud ]

07:00.721 --> 07:02.457
Hey, Gina.

07:04.501 --> 07:05.823
Everything alright?

07:05.823 --> 07:07.116
No.

07:07.116 --> 07:08.242
How could you not
run that by me?

07:09.660 --> 07:11.412
It's just a commercial.

07:11.412 --> 07:13.831
A <i>national</i> commercial.

07:13.831 --> 07:16.792
About our life.
That everyone's gonna see.

07:18.335 --> 07:19.128
I ‐‐

07:21.255 --> 07:23.591
Hey, uh, how was that?
Was it believable?

07:23.591 --> 07:25.301
Apparently.

07:25.301 --> 07:28.929
♪♪

07:32.218 --> 07:33.553
Sweet dreams, Charlotte.

07:35.471 --> 07:37.625
Okay. She's down.

07:37.625 --> 07:39.210
Look, I pulled up
Seymour's number.

07:39.210 --> 07:40.461
Call him.

07:40.461 --> 07:42.338
Maybe he can do something
this week.

07:42.338 --> 07:44.006
Hey, have you guys
seen my wallet?

07:44.006 --> 07:45.716
[ Line ringing ]
Oh. I can help you
look for it.

07:45.716 --> 07:47.593
Uh, nope. He's on.

07:47.593 --> 07:49.053
Seymour: <i>Hello?</i>

07:49.053 --> 07:49.970
<i>Hello?</i>

07:49.970 --> 07:52.515
Seymour, hi.
It's Delilah Dixon.

07:52.515 --> 07:54.016
[ Chuckling ]
Delilah Dixon?

07:54.016 --> 07:55.392
What, are you kidding?

07:55.392 --> 07:57.520
You're the only Delilah
in my life.

07:57.520 --> 08:00.397
Terrence, you gave me
the wrong contact sheet!

08:00.397 --> 08:02.775
How are you, honey?
How's the family?

08:02.775 --> 08:05.444
Um....well, actually,
that's why I was calling.

08:05.444 --> 08:07.738
I, um, just had a baby.
[ Chuckles ]

08:07.738 --> 08:09.990
Oh, honey,
that's wonderful.

08:09.990 --> 08:12.952
No wonder I didn't
hear from you at Christmas.

08:12.952 --> 08:14.745
I feel like no one's
helping me look here.

08:14.745 --> 08:17.039
You do know <i>Mom's</i> paying
for the photographer, right?

08:17.039 --> 08:19.125
<i>So, what can I do</i>
<i>for you, honey?</i>

08:19.125 --> 08:20.251
Um, y‐yeah.

08:20.251 --> 08:22.294
The kids were wondering
if you could come over

08:22.294 --> 08:25.256
and take a family photo
for the birth announcement.

08:25.256 --> 08:28.467
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm leaving for
Cozumel tomorrow for two weeks.

08:28.467 --> 08:31.345
But as soon as I come back,
I'm yours, okay?

08:31.345 --> 08:34.265
Just tell Jon
don't cut the hair too short

08:34.265 --> 08:36.183
<i>because it takes forever</i>
<i>to airbrush</i>

08:36.183 --> 08:39.562
<i>and, to be honest, it's not</i>
<i>Terrence's strong suit.</i>

08:41.272 --> 08:42.565
Uh, Seymour, actually,

08:42.565 --> 08:44.942
the reason you didn't
hear from us over the holidays

08:44.942 --> 08:46.527
is, um...

08:46.527 --> 08:49.321
is because Jon passed away
in October.

08:50.489 --> 08:52.158
Oh, sweetie.

08:52.158 --> 08:54.452
I'm sorry.
<i>Thank you.</i>

08:54.452 --> 08:57.538
Maybe we could schedule
something for when you get back.

08:57.538 --> 08:58.747
Terrence!

08:58.747 --> 09:00.040
Cancel my day.

09:00.040 --> 09:02.293
I'm coming over
this afternoon.

09:02.293 --> 09:05.087
<i>We're taking a picture of your</i>
<i>beautiful baby today, Delilah.</i>

09:05.087 --> 09:06.881
Rome: One minute,
she's kissing me,

09:06.881 --> 09:08.048
and then the next minute,
she's storming out.

09:08.048 --> 09:09.800
I don't get it.

09:09.800 --> 09:11.844
The commercial's only <i>loosely</i>
based on us, you know?

09:11.844 --> 09:14.013
Um, if anyone needs me,
I'm just stepping out
to make a quick call.

09:14.013 --> 09:14.930
Thanks, Andrea.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.476
Is that the actress
playing the character

09:18.476 --> 09:20.269
who's "loosely"
based on Regina?

09:20.269 --> 09:21.312
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:21.312 --> 09:22.813
'Cause if
Gina committed a crime,

09:22.813 --> 09:24.440
that woman gets stopped
for questioning.

09:24.440 --> 09:25.983
Can we change the subject?
Absolutely.

09:25.983 --> 09:27.276
I'm uncomfortable
with any conversation

09:27.276 --> 09:29.236
where <i>he's</i> in
the best relationship.

09:29.236 --> 09:31.280
Well, then,
you'll be glad to know

09:31.280 --> 09:32.781
that Katherine
wants to leave again.

09:32.781 --> 09:33.824
What?

09:33.824 --> 09:36.118
Last night, I saw
her search history.

09:36.118 --> 09:38.579
No, those guys are ‐‐
they're just bigger.

09:39.788 --> 09:42.458
No. She was looking up
the top 10 places to live.

09:42.458 --> 09:43.584
How does that mean
that she ‐‐

09:43.584 --> 09:45.127
Number one was Austin.

09:45.127 --> 09:47.004
She had
all these searches open ‐‐

09:47.004 --> 09:50.299
law jobs in Texas,
real‐estate listings.

09:51.800 --> 09:54.678
Okay. What did she say
when you asked her about it?

09:54.678 --> 09:56.013
I didn't.

09:56.013 --> 09:57.765
I was afraid of the answer.

09:57.765 --> 09:59.225
You got to talk to her
about this.

09:59.225 --> 10:01.060
Or produce a commercial

10:01.060 --> 10:03.354
about the exact situation
that you're <i>not</i> talking about

10:03.354 --> 10:04.730
and have her
visit the set.

10:08.192 --> 10:09.401
And in two hours,

10:09.401 --> 10:12.613
he's gonna be over
to take a family photo,

10:12.613 --> 10:15.324
which feels weird to do
without Jon.

10:15.324 --> 10:18.953
Well, you know, maybe don't
think of it as a family photo.

10:18.953 --> 10:21.747
Think of it
as Charlie's birth announcement.

10:21.747 --> 10:24.083
Which feels weird to do
without Eddie.

10:24.083 --> 10:26.085
Your life
is very complicated.

10:26.085 --> 10:27.336
It really is.

10:27.336 --> 10:28.420
[ Chuckles ]

10:29.588 --> 10:33.509
But the whole reason we decided
Charlie was gonna be Jon's baby

10:33.509 --> 10:36.679
is so that things like this
would be easier for the kids.

10:36.679 --> 10:38.681
Yeah. I get it.

10:38.681 --> 10:41.016
Moving on is hard.

10:41.016 --> 10:44.311
When my brother was still alive,
every Christmas,

10:44.311 --> 10:47.439
my family would rent this cabin
on Pontoosuc Lake.

10:47.439 --> 10:51.860
And at 11:59
on New Year's,

10:51.860 --> 10:54.697
Chad would get us all
to go down for a midnight swim.

10:54.697 --> 10:57.074
Oh, boy. [ Laughs ]
Yeah. It was freezing.

10:57.074 --> 10:59.159
But we would all
run down there,

10:59.159 --> 11:02.413
all four of us together,
and jump in.

11:02.413 --> 11:04.582
After...

11:04.582 --> 11:06.375
After he died,
we stopped going.

11:06.375 --> 11:09.837
It just...
didn't feel right.

11:09.837 --> 11:11.505
[ Inhales shakily ]

11:11.505 --> 11:14.300
But, you know,
a part of me always wished

11:14.300 --> 11:16.302
that we had kept
doing it.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.930
'Cause...

11:19.930 --> 11:22.391
if we had, maybe my family
would be in a better place.

11:22.391 --> 11:25.060
♪♪

11:25.060 --> 11:26.604
So, when he presents her
with the gift,

11:26.604 --> 11:27.855
bring out
the champagne flutes.
Mm‐hmm.

11:27.855 --> 11:29.315
Unless the gift
is not the cruise.

11:29.315 --> 11:30.733
In which case,

11:30.733 --> 11:32.943
get anything made of glass
away from that woman.

11:32.943 --> 11:34.111
[ Chuckling ]
Okay. Got it.

11:34.111 --> 11:36.071
Wow.

11:36.071 --> 11:38.699
The place looks amazing.
They are going to love it, babe.

11:38.699 --> 11:41.035
So, you're just not
gonna mention anything

11:41.035 --> 11:42.620
about what happened
earlier?

11:42.620 --> 11:44.913
I'm sorry
if the commercial upset you.

11:44.913 --> 11:47.666
Don't say "if"
like I'm crazy for being upset.

11:47.666 --> 11:49.335
But it's not our story.
[ Scoffs ]

11:49.335 --> 11:50.210
It's a whole
different ending.

11:50.210 --> 11:51.920
Yeah, it <i>is.</i>

11:51.920 --> 11:54.214
Which makes me feel like it's
a real passive‐aggressive way ‐‐

11:54.214 --> 11:55.341
Walter:
Special delivery.

11:55.341 --> 11:57.134
That's his way
of telling you

11:57.134 --> 11:59.470
he parked
in the Deliveries Only space.

11:59.470 --> 12:01.764
$9 for valet parking.

12:01.764 --> 12:03.265
That's what
<i>dinner</i> should cost.

12:03.265 --> 12:04.767
[ Laughs ]
Happy anniversary.

12:04.767 --> 12:06.560
Who's ready
to celebrate?

12:07.770 --> 12:09.229
Maggie:
I still dream about him.

12:09.229 --> 12:11.357
They're so vivid.

12:11.357 --> 12:16.153
I only call them dreams
so that people don't lock me up.

12:16.153 --> 12:17.738
[ Both chuckle ]

12:17.738 --> 12:19.281
Do you ever dream
about Jon?

12:19.281 --> 12:21.909
Mm. I used to.

12:21.909 --> 12:24.119
And then
they just stopped.

12:24.119 --> 12:26.997
[ Chuckling ] Why do you think
I had us go to that psychic?

12:26.997 --> 12:30.876
♪♪

12:30.876 --> 12:32.127
What is it?

12:34.880 --> 12:36.215
Um...

12:38.092 --> 12:39.468
[ Sighs ]

12:39.468 --> 12:43.597
Do you remember
what the psychic said,

12:43.597 --> 12:47.101
that a part of Chad
lives on?

12:47.101 --> 12:48.560
Yeah, of course.

12:50.229 --> 12:53.649
[ Voice breaking ]
Do you think that, um...

12:56.068 --> 12:57.444
...he meant
my brother's heart?

12:57.444 --> 12:59.154
Do you think
he meant Eric?

12:59.154 --> 13:02.991
♪♪

13:02.991 --> 13:06.829
I knew that I was going to
marry this man

13:06.829 --> 13:08.747
the moment
I first laid eyes on him.

13:08.747 --> 13:12.418
You were so handsome
in your dress blues.

13:12.418 --> 13:14.420
I was going off to Da Nang,

13:14.420 --> 13:15.796
and I would have been fine

13:15.796 --> 13:18.257
if you were the last thing
I ever saw.

13:18.257 --> 13:20.592
Regina: Ohh!
Oh, Walter, that's so sweet.

13:20.592 --> 13:22.302
Well, he's got
the great lines.

13:22.302 --> 13:24.555
Let's see if he's got
the great gifts.

13:24.555 --> 13:26.765
Ooh! Did somebody
say "gifts"?

13:26.765 --> 13:29.059
I hope I'm getting
what I hope I'm getting.

13:29.059 --> 13:30.936
[ Paper rustling ]

13:30.936 --> 13:34.606
This is for you, Renee,
for 50 wonderful years.

13:36.108 --> 13:37.708
Is this clothes?

13:37.708 --> 13:38.544
Oh, God.

13:40.796 --> 13:42.631
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, thank God.

13:42.631 --> 13:44.007
[ Chuckling ]
You didn't!

13:44.007 --> 13:44.758
I did.

13:44.758 --> 13:46.260
He did.
He did!

13:46.260 --> 13:50.222
Ooh, I'm gonna have to be
really clear now.

13:50.222 --> 13:55.686
This <i>is</i> the Alaskan cruise
I've always wanted to go on?

13:55.686 --> 13:59.648
Renee...this is the cruise
you've always wanted.

13:59.648 --> 14:01.775
The one you've been
asking about every year

14:01.775 --> 14:04.194
for the last
God knows how long.

14:04.194 --> 14:06.864
You wanted to do this,
so we're doing it.

14:06.864 --> 14:09.116
Seven days, seven nights.

14:09.116 --> 14:10.158
Ooh!

14:10.158 --> 14:12.035
And then we dock.

14:12.035 --> 14:15.038
At which point, I never
want to hear about it again.

14:17.124 --> 14:19.334
Really?
What?

14:19.334 --> 14:24.047
This is how you're giving me
the gift I've been asking for

14:24.047 --> 14:26.592
for the last
"God knows how long"?

14:26.592 --> 14:29.553
The point is, we're going
on your stupid cruise.

14:29.553 --> 14:30.929
Unbelievable.

14:30.929 --> 14:32.514
Let's toast.
To 50 years!
[ Clears throat ]

14:35.677 --> 14:38.439
Renee: Well, you shouldn't
have given it to me if you
didn't want to give it to me.

14:38.439 --> 14:39.937
Well, maybe the only reason
I gave it to you

14:39.937 --> 14:41.063
is because you made me feel
guilty <i>not</i> giving it to you.

14:41.063 --> 14:42.023
Dad!
Renee.

14:42.023 --> 14:43.441
You just can't please
this woman.

14:43.441 --> 14:46.027
Walter Howard, you are wrecking
my anniversary luncheon.

14:46.027 --> 14:47.904
If you're gonna
keep acting like this,

14:47.904 --> 14:49.530
you might as well leave.

14:49.530 --> 14:51.032
Fine!

14:51.032 --> 14:52.408
Rome: No ‐‐

14:52.408 --> 14:55.578
Regina, Rome, thank you
for a wonderful meal.

14:55.578 --> 14:57.371
I assume
the house will get this.

14:57.371 --> 14:59.123
Where are you going?

14:59.123 --> 15:00.249
Not on a cruise.

15:00.249 --> 15:01.584
Dad ‐‐

15:01.584 --> 15:03.002
Mom.

15:03.002 --> 15:04.045
People!

15:04.045 --> 15:05.505
Gary: Nine months ago,

15:05.505 --> 15:08.007
I sat here
as a‐a breast cancer survivor.

15:10.009 --> 15:13.721
Today, I'm sitting here
as someone who is...

15:13.721 --> 15:18.100
in love with
a breast cancer survivor.

15:18.100 --> 15:21.270
So, I gotta ask...

15:21.270 --> 15:26.442
how do you support someone
when their cancer is gone?

15:30.279 --> 15:31.697
Can I say something?

15:31.697 --> 15:32.949
Tessa.

15:32.949 --> 15:36.244
I've known you for, what,
like, two years now, Gary?

15:36.244 --> 15:38.079
Two amazing years.
Sure.

15:38.079 --> 15:39.580
And in those two years,

15:39.580 --> 15:42.583
you sat here
talking about your cancer

15:42.583 --> 15:45.878
like you knew for sure
it was coming back.

15:45.878 --> 15:48.589
You always said, "It's not
that I don't have cancer.

15:48.589 --> 15:49.799
It's that..."

15:49.799 --> 15:52.593
Together: "I don't have cancer
right now."

15:52.593 --> 15:54.387
Okay, so, apparently,
I've said that before.

15:54.387 --> 15:56.013
[ Laughter ]

15:56.013 --> 16:00.059
So, my point is,
listen to your own words.

16:00.059 --> 16:01.519
Which words?

16:01.519 --> 16:03.354
Tessa,
I say a lot of things.

16:03.354 --> 16:05.147
[ Laughter ]

16:05.147 --> 16:08.192
You said
that for survivors,

16:08.192 --> 16:11.153
there is no life
without cancer.

16:11.153 --> 16:12.947
And you're right.

16:12.947 --> 16:16.867
And some people want to sit here
and talk about that,

16:16.867 --> 16:18.286
and other people don't.

16:18.286 --> 16:20.329
♪♪

16:20.329 --> 16:24.458
Maggie didn't miss today
because she was busy, Gary.

16:24.458 --> 16:26.085
She missed today
because...

16:26.085 --> 16:28.736
she wants to move on.

16:28.736 --> 16:36.911
♪♪

16:36.911 --> 16:38.329
[ Bell jingles ]

16:39.580 --> 16:40.748
Maggie.

16:40.748 --> 16:42.503
What‐‐ What's wrong?

16:44.588 --> 16:46.715
[ Voice breaking ]
Um...

16:46.715 --> 16:48.968
[ Bell jingles ]
I just, uh...

16:48.968 --> 16:50.261
I ju‐‐

16:50.261 --> 16:51.762
[ Sobbing ]

16:51.762 --> 16:55.599
♪♪

16:55.599 --> 16:57.309
G‐‐ I'm sorry.

16:57.309 --> 16:58.644
I just ‐‐ No.
[ Sniffles ]
No, uh...

16:58.644 --> 17:01.981
I was looking up
these pictures of this place

17:01.981 --> 17:04.233
that my family used to rent
on Pontoosuc Lake,

17:04.233 --> 17:06.193
and I couldn't
remember it,

17:06.193 --> 17:08.779
and I can't believe
I can't remember,

17:08.779 --> 17:12.366
because all I want to do
is remember.

17:12.366 --> 17:14.660
I just miss him.

17:14.660 --> 17:16.370
Yeah, I ‐‐

17:16.370 --> 17:18.247
Here.

17:18.247 --> 17:19.498
I just...

17:19.498 --> 17:20.499
[ Sobs ]

17:20.499 --> 17:22.585
I miss him so much.

17:24.211 --> 17:25.629
[ Door opens ]

17:31.760 --> 17:33.345
What's going on?

17:33.345 --> 17:34.805
[ Keys thud ]

17:34.805 --> 17:36.640
I saw
your search history.

17:39.435 --> 17:40.853
Last night in Theo's room,

17:40.853 --> 17:42.938
when I was looking up
woolly mammoths.

17:42.938 --> 17:47.443
I was afraid to ask then,
but now I need to know.

17:47.443 --> 17:49.695
Do you want to move
to Austin?

17:51.071 --> 17:53.407
♪♪

17:53.407 --> 17:55.618
Yeah. I do.

17:55.618 --> 17:59.121
♪♪

17:59.121 --> 18:02.124
But I want you and Theo
to come with me.

18:02.124 --> 18:06.587
♪♪

18:06.587 --> 18:09.089
It's so...

18:09.089 --> 18:12.218
hard to do this, Eddie.

18:15.304 --> 18:18.057
And it's even harder with
everyone knowing our business.

18:19.683 --> 18:21.685
Sometimes I just wonder
what it would be like

18:21.685 --> 18:24.230
if we had a fresh start.

18:27.107 --> 18:28.943
We'd still have to deal
with all our stuff,

18:28.943 --> 18:31.862
but at least it would just be
<i>us</i> dealing with it,

18:31.862 --> 18:34.323
not a bunch of people
wondering how we're doing it

18:34.323 --> 18:35.866
or why we're doing it.

18:37.701 --> 18:39.370
So, the other night,

18:39.370 --> 18:43.082
I...looked at some places
that we could start over.

18:45.417 --> 18:49.004
I've never been to Austin,
but...

18:49.004 --> 18:50.714
I wish we lived there.

18:54.468 --> 18:56.303
But I know we can't.
[ Clears throat ]

18:56.303 --> 18:57.888
'Cause you have to be here
for Charlie.

19:01.016 --> 19:02.726
We can't go to Austin.

19:04.812 --> 19:06.522
But there is someplace
we <i>can</i> go.

19:08.315 --> 19:09.942
Come on.

19:09.942 --> 19:14.989
♪♪

19:14.989 --> 19:16.198
[ Chuckles ]

19:16.198 --> 19:17.825
Yeah.

19:17.825 --> 19:19.493
Mom,
h‐h‐here's the deal.

19:19.493 --> 19:22.663
Right now, Regina's in
the kitchen, talking to Dad,

19:22.663 --> 19:25.708
making him realize
that he wants to apologize.

19:27.251 --> 19:29.753
All I need for you to do
is just...

19:29.753 --> 19:33.841
put yourself in a position
to hear it.

19:33.841 --> 19:36.635
Well, I don't want him
to apologize

19:36.635 --> 19:40.097
if he's not <i>ready</i>
to apologize.

19:40.097 --> 19:41.557
Okay.

19:41.557 --> 19:43.392
I see
you have work to do there.

19:43.392 --> 19:44.935
Why should I be the one
to apologize?

19:44.935 --> 19:46.228
I gave her
what she wanted.

19:46.228 --> 19:47.980
Okay, I'm gonna
go out on a limb here

19:47.980 --> 19:51.025
and say that's <i>not</i>
what she wanted.

19:51.025 --> 19:53.861
Yes, Renee has been asking
to go on this cruise for years,

19:53.861 --> 19:55.446
but the reason she's upset
is because

19:55.446 --> 19:57.781
she wants to go on it
with <i>you.</i>

19:57.781 --> 20:00.784
To take that journey
together.

20:00.784 --> 20:03.704
Don't you think
she deserves to have this?

20:03.704 --> 20:06.457
Let me ask you something.

20:06.457 --> 20:08.709
Rome ever ask you to do
something you didn't want to do?

20:08.709 --> 20:13.130
♪♪

20:13.130 --> 20:14.757
He has.

20:14.757 --> 20:16.050
And did you do it?

20:18.218 --> 20:19.345
I did not.

20:19.345 --> 20:22.097
See?
She's being ridiculous.

20:22.097 --> 20:24.516
And this is not how
I want to celebrate
my anniversary, either.

20:24.516 --> 20:26.352
Whatever it was with Rome,

20:26.352 --> 20:27.853
you were right
to stand up to him,

20:27.853 --> 20:29.313
and I should do the same
with Renee.

20:29.313 --> 20:30.314
Dad.

20:30.314 --> 20:31.648
Walter ‐‐
Come on!

20:33.901 --> 20:35.277
Okay.

20:35.277 --> 20:36.403
I've thought about it,

20:36.403 --> 20:38.947
and I'm ready
to hear the apology.

20:38.947 --> 20:41.325
♪♪

20:45.327 --> 20:46.370
Where are we going?

20:46.370 --> 20:48.122
Just trust me.

20:48.122 --> 20:49.498
[ Door opens ]

20:51.625 --> 20:54.503
What are we
doing here?

20:54.503 --> 20:56.547
‐Hello?
‐Hi.

20:56.547 --> 20:58.173
We're here
for the open house.

20:58.173 --> 20:59.925
Hi.
I'm ‐‐ I'm Tammy Blakely.

20:59.925 --> 21:01.718
Tammy, hi.
I'm Edward.

21:01.718 --> 21:04.388
This is my wife, Kat.

21:04.388 --> 21:06.140
We're thinking
of moving here.

21:06.140 --> 21:07.432
Oh, how wonderful.

21:07.432 --> 21:09.476
Well,
let me show you around.

21:09.476 --> 21:10.602
Where, uh ‐‐
Where are you moving from?

21:12.187 --> 21:13.230
Austin.

21:13.230 --> 21:14.565
Oh. Nice.

21:17.317 --> 21:19.111
[ Scales playing ]
Eric: Max will help you
take this to your car.

21:19.111 --> 21:20.612
Yeah, I got you.

21:20.612 --> 21:22.656
Eric's got
no upper‐body strength.

21:22.656 --> 21:24.491
It's true.

21:24.491 --> 21:25.784
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks, Max.

21:25.784 --> 21:27.119
[ Bell jingles ]

21:27.119 --> 21:28.996
Oh, that's right.
You play.

21:28.996 --> 21:30.414
Oh. Yeah.

21:30.414 --> 21:31.373
You?

21:31.373 --> 21:32.875
Not even a little.
No.

21:32.875 --> 21:34.001
No guitar?

21:34.001 --> 21:35.210
God, no.

21:35.210 --> 21:36.712
Do you play an instrument?

21:36.712 --> 21:38.005
Oh, you mean
'cause I own a music store?

21:38.005 --> 21:39.298
Yeah,
I‐I get that a lot.

21:39.298 --> 21:40.632
Nope.
[ Both chuckle ]

21:40.632 --> 21:45.095
Um, no, this was, um ‐‐
this was Chloe's...store, so...

21:47.890 --> 21:49.850
How'd you guys meet?

21:49.850 --> 21:51.435
[ Chuckling ] Um...

21:51.435 --> 21:53.687
actually, I met her
right over there.

21:53.687 --> 21:54.730
Aw.

21:54.730 --> 21:57.316
Um, I‐I would see her
a‐at this, uh ‐‐

21:57.316 --> 21:59.318
the coffee shop
around the corner all the time,

21:59.318 --> 22:01.695
but I didn't have the courage
to go up to her,

22:01.695 --> 22:04.740
so, I, uh...
I did the less creepy thing

22:04.740 --> 22:06.533
and figured out
where she worked.

22:06.533 --> 22:07.743
[ Chuckles ]

22:07.743 --> 22:10.829
And I took out a monthly rental
on a clarinet.

22:10.829 --> 22:12.122
It came with lessons.

22:12.122 --> 22:13.373
From Chloe.

22:13.373 --> 22:15.500
No, from Max.
It was very awkward.

22:15.500 --> 22:16.501
[ Laughs ]

22:16.501 --> 22:18.420
[ Chuckling ]
But, um, eventually, I...

22:18.420 --> 22:21.006
got up the courage
to ask her out.

22:21.006 --> 22:22.257
[ Chuckles ]

22:25.636 --> 22:27.262
I used to play
for my brother.

22:27.262 --> 22:29.139
Mm.
[ Chuckles ]

22:29.139 --> 22:31.600
He would pretend
to sit in the front row

22:31.600 --> 22:34.311
of a concert that I was playing
for thousands of people.

22:34.311 --> 22:35.479
[ Chuckles ]

22:35.479 --> 22:37.648
And Chad would tell me

22:37.648 --> 22:39.483
[ Keyboard playing ]
to focus on him

22:39.483 --> 22:42.444
so that I wouldn't get
stage fright.

22:44.696 --> 22:46.365
Have you ever played
a real concert?

22:46.365 --> 22:48.158
No. And, um...

22:48.158 --> 22:49.409
[ Sour chord plays ]

22:49.409 --> 22:51.536
[ Chuckling ]
...I'm very rusty.

22:51.536 --> 22:52.788
[ Chuckles ]

22:52.788 --> 22:54.539
I haven't played
since I got sick.

22:54.539 --> 22:55.666
Why not?

22:56.917 --> 22:58.335
Uh...

22:58.335 --> 23:00.587
Well, the first time,

23:00.587 --> 23:04.049
I focused all of my energy
on getting better.

23:05.717 --> 23:07.761
I stopped doing
a <i>lot</i> of things.

23:07.761 --> 23:11.515
And then
I got sick again.

23:11.515 --> 23:13.058
Well,
you're not sick anymore.

23:13.058 --> 23:16.270
Maybe it's time to pick back up
where you left off.

23:17.938 --> 23:19.314
[ Gasps ]

23:19.314 --> 23:21.400
You know, um...

23:21.400 --> 23:26.613
there is a piano bar
a couple blocks from here

23:26.613 --> 23:28.865
that does
an open‐mic night.

23:30.284 --> 23:32.953
I can sit in the front row
so you don't get stage fright.

23:32.953 --> 23:33.954
[ Chuckles ]

23:33.954 --> 23:36.039
[ Chuckles ]

23:36.039 --> 23:39.167
Not gonna lie, this closet ‐‐
bigger than my first apartment.

23:39.167 --> 23:40.460
[ Chuckles ]
Oh.

23:40.460 --> 23:43.964
Our first apartment
was just outside Houston.

23:43.964 --> 23:45.090
Oh, that's right.

23:45.090 --> 23:47.175
That was right after
you got into the academy.

23:47.175 --> 23:48.427
Oh. Naval?

23:48.427 --> 23:49.469
Space.

23:50.721 --> 23:53.932
You never really understand
how beautiful the Earth is

23:53.932 --> 23:55.851
until you've seen it
from where I've seen it.

23:55.851 --> 23:58.478
Man: Hello? Tammy?

23:58.478 --> 24:00.188
Oh. Can you excuse me
for a second?

24:00.188 --> 24:03.066
There's a couple that's back
to look at the house.

24:03.066 --> 24:04.693
I think they're gonna
make an offer,

24:04.693 --> 24:07.404
so if you're interested,
you should move quickly.

24:07.404 --> 24:08.405
Katherine: Thanks.

24:10.699 --> 24:12.868
Hello!
Welcome back.

24:12.868 --> 24:15.329
Is it too late for me
to adopt a Texan accent?

24:15.329 --> 24:17.205
[ Texan accent ]
I reckon it is,

24:17.205 --> 24:19.124
but I say
go for it, par'ner.

24:19.124 --> 24:20.500
[ Both chuckle ]

24:20.500 --> 24:22.878
[ Normal voice ]
Thanks, Edward.

24:22.878 --> 24:24.504
This is
just what I needed.

24:24.504 --> 24:30.302
♪♪

24:30.302 --> 24:36.350
♪♪

24:36.350 --> 24:40.062
[ Texan accent ] Can I show you
the walk‐in closet?

24:41.063 --> 24:42.773
Really?

24:42.773 --> 24:44.733
[ Normal voice ] Well, she did
say we need to move quickly.

24:44.733 --> 24:51.490
♪♪

24:51.490 --> 24:53.617
Delilah:
Let's just take this. It's
almost time for Charlie's nap.

24:53.617 --> 24:55.994
Perfect!
Just take a casual pose.

24:55.994 --> 24:58.914
Daniel, you look very dapper.
I love that blazer.

24:58.914 --> 25:02.417
I‐I‐I really don't want
to take this ‐‐

25:02.417 --> 25:03.710
not until
I find my wallet.

25:03.710 --> 25:05.629
Sweetie, I'll help you
find it after, okay,

25:05.629 --> 25:07.047
but right now,
we have a small window

25:07.047 --> 25:09.007
till Charlie just...
has a meltdown.

25:09.007 --> 25:10.342
So please, okay?

25:10.342 --> 25:11.968
Come on, Soph,
let's go.

25:11.968 --> 25:14.304
Okay.

25:14.304 --> 25:17.724
Ohh! Would you look
at that beautiful flower.

25:17.724 --> 25:20.143
[ Charlie crying ]
You know
what I would love to do?

25:20.143 --> 25:23.105
Put a headband on her so that
we know that she's a she.

25:23.105 --> 25:24.272
Sophie: I can go get one.

25:24.272 --> 25:25.440
No,
we're losing our window.

25:25.440 --> 25:27.192
[ Knock on door ]
Gosh!

25:27.192 --> 25:28.902
Okay, two seconds.

25:28.902 --> 25:30.320
Danny,
stay right there.

25:31.822 --> 25:33.240
Hi.
Hi.

25:33.240 --> 25:35.117
I'm looking for
Jonathan Dixon.

25:35.117 --> 25:39.079
♪♪

25:42.745 --> 25:46.376
I work at Electrazone,
the arcade out in West Newton?

25:46.376 --> 25:47.584
Okay?

25:47.584 --> 25:49.071
Uh, this was the address
on his license.

25:49.071 --> 25:50.111
That's mine!

25:52.614 --> 25:54.157
Oh. Great.

25:54.157 --> 25:55.784
Well, thank you so much
for returning it.

25:55.784 --> 25:56.785
Oh, no, no, no.
Please.

25:56.785 --> 25:58.286
[ Chuckles ]
My pleasure.

25:58.286 --> 25:59.496
Thank you.

25:59.496 --> 26:01.706
You had Dad's license?

26:01.706 --> 26:03.375
Sweetie?

26:03.375 --> 26:05.836
I thought if I had the license
in my wallet,

26:05.836 --> 26:08.421
Dad could be in the picture
without you knowing.

26:08.421 --> 26:09.923
But the truth is,

26:09.923 --> 26:12.676
we shouldn't be doing this
without him.

26:12.676 --> 26:15.136
And I'm not going to.

26:15.136 --> 26:15.929
Danny.

26:15.929 --> 26:18.181
No!
I'm not going to!

26:18.181 --> 26:19.474
Danny,
can we please just ‐‐

26:19.474 --> 26:20.475
[ Sighs ]

26:20.475 --> 26:21.601
[ Door slams ]

26:21.601 --> 26:25.522
♪♪

26:25.522 --> 26:26.565
[ Sighs ]

26:26.565 --> 26:34.281
♪♪

26:34.281 --> 26:35.574
[ Sighs ]

26:35.574 --> 26:42.080
♪♪

26:42.080 --> 26:48.461
♪♪

26:48.461 --> 26:49.713
[ Sighs ]

26:52.757 --> 26:55.260
Oh, Seymour, I'm sorry
I had you waste your time.

26:55.260 --> 26:57.304
Oh, don't be ridiculous.

26:57.304 --> 27:00.140
Look, if you change your mind,
I'm always here for you.

27:01.182 --> 27:04.102
Except the next two weeks,
when I'll be in Cozumel.

27:04.102 --> 27:06.813
Which I <i>really</i> need
right now.

27:06.813 --> 27:08.773
I love you guys.
I'll call you when I get back.

27:08.773 --> 27:11.693
Sophie: Come on! Fine!
I was just trying to help!

27:11.693 --> 27:15.196
But just so you know, we already
have a baby in the house!

27:15.196 --> 27:17.240
Okay, I cannot believe
he won't come out of his room

27:17.240 --> 27:18.658
to take one stupid photo.

27:18.658 --> 27:21.745
Well, honestly, honey...

27:21.745 --> 27:24.122
I'm not sure I was ready
to take it, either.

27:24.122 --> 27:25.332
Oh ‐‐ Oh, so, what?

27:25.332 --> 27:27.709
Now we're just gonna
never take a photo again?

27:27.709 --> 27:29.336
Soph! Come on.

27:29.336 --> 27:31.046
Sophie, please.
That's not what I'm saying.

27:31.046 --> 27:32.130
[ Door slams ]

27:32.130 --> 27:33.715
[ Cellphone buzzing ]
[ Scoffs ]

27:37.302 --> 27:38.970
[ Buzzing stops ]

27:38.970 --> 27:41.181
Maggie, hi.
Is everything okay?

27:41.181 --> 27:44.100
Yeah. It's, uh...
it's...good, actually.

27:44.100 --> 27:46.686
Um, how'd things go
with the photo?

27:46.686 --> 27:48.146
<i>Not as good.</i>

27:48.146 --> 27:49.606
Danny's upset
because we're doing it.

27:49.606 --> 27:51.775
Sophie's upset because
we're <i>not</i> doing it.

27:51.775 --> 27:55.153
So not...
a perfect situation.

27:56.488 --> 27:59.032
You know, you remember
what I was saying earlier

27:59.032 --> 28:01.868
about my family's trips
to the lake?

28:01.868 --> 28:06.122
I‐I understand why we stopped
going after Chad died.

28:06.122 --> 28:09.459
I mean, it was just too hard
for my parents

28:09.459 --> 28:11.461
<i>to do something</i>
<i>without their son</i>

28:11.461 --> 28:13.588
<i>that they used to do</i>
<i>with him.</i>

28:13.588 --> 28:15.340
Yeah.

28:15.340 --> 28:18.968
What we should have done
was start a <i>new</i> tradition.

28:20.178 --> 28:22.764
<i>One that let us know</i>
<i>that we were still a family.</i>

28:22.764 --> 28:26.518
♪♪

28:26.518 --> 28:28.103
Delilah:
And I know this is hard,

28:28.103 --> 28:30.397
and there are
just so many things

28:30.397 --> 28:33.441
that we used to do with Dad
that he's not here for anymore.

28:33.441 --> 28:35.860
It just feels like we're trying
to move on without him.

28:35.860 --> 28:37.487
Well, yeah. What?

28:37.487 --> 28:39.406
Are we just gonna sit around
and be sad about what happened

28:39.406 --> 28:40.699
for the rest
of our lives?

28:40.699 --> 28:43.243
I'm not sad. I just
don't want to forget Dad.

28:43.243 --> 28:44.536
Don't you miss him?

28:44.536 --> 28:47.455
Of course I miss him.
I miss him all the time!

28:47.455 --> 28:49.207
Okay, stop.

28:49.207 --> 28:50.667
Nobody's trying
to forget him.

28:52.419 --> 28:55.839
And we all miss him.
We all miss him all the time.

28:57.549 --> 28:59.634
Danny, if you need to keep
a picture of him in your wallet,

28:59.634 --> 29:01.803
you should.

29:01.803 --> 29:03.888
But Sophie's right, too.

29:03.888 --> 29:05.640
And it's so hard
to imagine

29:05.640 --> 29:08.393
taking a family photo
without him.

29:08.393 --> 29:10.270
But Dad would want us
to take a picture

29:10.270 --> 29:12.021
for Charlie's
birth announcement.

29:12.021 --> 29:13.356
Right?

29:15.108 --> 29:17.277
He would want us
to still be a family.

29:17.277 --> 29:18.319
[ Charlie coos ]

29:18.319 --> 29:20.405
♪ 'Cause I feel love ♪

29:20.405 --> 29:22.365
See?
Even Charlie agrees.

29:22.365 --> 29:24.617
♪ Throwing it all away ♪

29:24.617 --> 29:26.995
♪ I'm sleepless ♪

29:26.995 --> 29:28.830
Can you come downstairs
with me?

29:28.830 --> 29:31.082
♪♪

29:31.082 --> 29:32.625
I want
to show you something.

29:34.502 --> 29:36.796
Danny:
What are we doing?

29:36.796 --> 29:39.382
We're starting
a new tradition.

29:39.382 --> 29:41.050
Well, look
who finally showed up.

29:41.050 --> 29:42.719
[ Laughter ]
Rome: Come on.

29:42.719 --> 29:45.597
It feels weird taking
a family photo without you.

29:45.597 --> 29:48.016
Thank you so much
for dropping everything

29:48.016 --> 29:50.727
and coming over
so quickly.

29:50.727 --> 29:53.521
After last year, when
the kids and I think of family,

29:53.521 --> 29:56.357
we ‐‐ we really do
think of you.

29:56.357 --> 29:57.609
All of you.

29:59.319 --> 30:01.196
I just couldn't have imagined
taking this photo

30:01.196 --> 30:03.782
for Charlie's birth announcement
without you in it.

30:05.492 --> 30:08.661
And, uh...thank you.

30:08.661 --> 30:09.954
Let's do it.
Alright. Come on.

30:09.954 --> 30:12.207
‐What's up, Charlie?
‐Kids in the front, please.

30:12.207 --> 30:13.249
Okay.

30:14.584 --> 30:16.628
Gather in.
Perfect.

30:16.628 --> 30:18.463
You got 12 seconds
to find your smiles.

30:18.463 --> 30:20.089
Oh.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

30:20.089 --> 30:21.925
Dad needs to be
in the picture.

30:21.925 --> 30:23.802
Everybody say "Cozumel."

30:23.802 --> 30:24.844
What?
What?

30:24.844 --> 30:26.638
Just say it.
Just say it.

30:26.638 --> 30:29.140
All: Cozumel!

30:29.140 --> 30:30.350
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

30:31.810 --> 30:33.603
So...

30:33.603 --> 30:36.231
I take it the anniversary lunch
didn't go so great?

30:37.315 --> 30:38.775
It did not.

30:40.235 --> 30:42.487
Sorry, pal.

30:42.487 --> 30:44.113
‐Here, Mom.
‐Thank you.

30:44.113 --> 30:45.949
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:45.949 --> 30:47.116
Thank you.
Here you go.

30:47.116 --> 30:48.785
Hey, bud?
I know!

30:48.785 --> 30:52.163
[ Deep voice ]
"Couch pillows aren't a napkin."

30:52.163 --> 30:56.459
♪ I made the walk
from Albany to Rome ♪

30:56.459 --> 30:57.794
Hi, Charlie!

30:57.794 --> 30:59.003
[ Charlie coos ]
Hey!

30:59.003 --> 31:04.592
♪♪

31:04.592 --> 31:08.680
♪ 'Cause I feel love ♪

31:08.680 --> 31:11.307
♪ Throwing it all away ♪

31:11.307 --> 31:14.185
♪ I'm sleepless ♪

31:14.185 --> 31:16.145
Get a room, huh?

31:16.145 --> 31:17.438
We almost got a house.

31:17.438 --> 31:18.606
[ Laughs ]

31:18.606 --> 31:19.732
I don't get it.

31:19.732 --> 31:22.485
[ Eddie and Katherine laugh ]

31:22.485 --> 31:23.945
This is what we like.

31:23.945 --> 31:25.738
We don't like shoes.

31:25.738 --> 31:28.283
This is
your charcuterie board.

31:28.283 --> 31:29.534
What's going on here?

31:29.534 --> 31:32.412
I'm just giving him a snack
to protect my footwear.

31:32.412 --> 31:33.997
Your lucky day, bud.

31:36.916 --> 31:40.503
Hey, can I ‐‐
can I ask you something?

31:40.503 --> 31:42.088
Yeah.

31:42.088 --> 31:45.091
Why didn't you go
to the remission group today?

31:45.091 --> 31:48.386
I told you. I was busy
staging the apartment.

31:48.386 --> 31:49.512
Are you sure
that's the reason?

31:49.512 --> 31:51.389
Because...

31:51.389 --> 31:53.975
everyone in the group
seemed to think that it's...

31:53.975 --> 31:55.476
because
you're avoiding it.

31:55.476 --> 31:56.477
[ Scoffs ]

31:56.477 --> 31:57.812
Wow.

31:57.812 --> 31:59.647
Great.
You solved it.

32:01.232 --> 32:02.859
[ Sighs ]

32:02.859 --> 32:04.360
I mean, what do you
want me to say?

32:06.154 --> 32:08.281
I want you to tell me
what's going on.

32:08.281 --> 32:12.327
♪♪

32:12.327 --> 32:14.454
Are we okay?

32:14.454 --> 32:15.830
What do you mean?

32:15.830 --> 32:18.750
I mean, y‐‐

32:18.750 --> 32:21.753
You ‐‐ You feel
pretty far away.

32:23.296 --> 32:24.547
It's just...

32:24.547 --> 32:28.843
I'm ‐‐ I'm trying to figure out
who we are...

32:28.843 --> 32:31.012
without cancer.

32:31.012 --> 32:33.348
Yeah, that's it, Gary.
Um...

32:36.225 --> 32:39.270
I'm still trying to figure out
who I am without cancer.

32:41.064 --> 32:43.524
I mean, there's so many things
that I wanted to do

32:43.524 --> 32:44.901
before I got sick.

32:44.901 --> 32:47.904
I used to play music.
I wanted to travel.

32:49.948 --> 32:51.741
You know
what I did today?

32:51.741 --> 32:54.327
I, um...

32:54.327 --> 32:58.373
I threw out all the plans
I'd made for my funeral.

32:58.373 --> 32:59.582
[ Pats table ]

32:59.582 --> 33:03.586
What song I wanted to play,
who should speak,

33:03.586 --> 33:06.255
what dress
I wanted to be buried in.

33:06.255 --> 33:10.009
I mean, most girls my age
are planning their weddings.

33:10.009 --> 33:11.552
You don't need
any of that stuff any‐‐

33:11.552 --> 33:12.303
No, I know.

33:12.303 --> 33:13.846
I know.

33:13.846 --> 33:15.139
I just...

33:17.850 --> 33:21.020
Since I met you,
I've been dying.

33:21.020 --> 33:22.105
[ Chuckles ]

33:23.898 --> 33:27.151
I really want
to get back to living.

33:27.151 --> 33:29.028
But I don't know how to do that.
[ Chuckles ]

33:29.028 --> 33:32.031
Let me help you figure it out.
That's why I'm here.

33:32.031 --> 33:32.824
Gary...

33:35.243 --> 33:36.244
...I love you.

33:37.912 --> 33:41.290
This is something
I need to do myself.

33:41.290 --> 33:49.048
♪♪

33:49.048 --> 33:56.472
♪♪

34:01.936 --> 34:03.062
[ Elevator bell dings ]

34:04.772 --> 34:06.607
Maybe you should
call him.

34:06.607 --> 34:09.068
He knows
how to reach me.

34:09.068 --> 34:12.488
I'm not going home
until he apologizes.

34:12.488 --> 34:14.824
Okay. I guess
I'll make up the couch.

34:14.824 --> 34:16.242
For <i>us.</i>

34:17.910 --> 34:20.079
Although I don't know
what he could possibly say

34:20.079 --> 34:21.497
to fix this.

34:21.497 --> 34:22.707
[ Elevator bell dings ]

34:22.707 --> 34:25.293
♪♪

34:25.293 --> 34:26.335
Walter: Renee.

34:28.212 --> 34:31.090
For 50 years,
you've put up with me.

34:31.090 --> 34:34.761
I don't know how you've done it
or why you've done it,

34:34.761 --> 34:37.555
but I'm glad
you've done it.

34:37.555 --> 34:40.266
And you deserve
everything you want.

34:42.477 --> 34:46.355
So, I would be honored if you'd
go on that cruise with me.

34:46.355 --> 34:47.857
[ Chuckles ]

34:47.857 --> 34:52.320
♪♪

34:52.320 --> 34:53.780
Walter.

34:53.780 --> 34:57.158
♪♪

34:57.158 --> 34:59.160
It's a good thing
he left before dessert,

34:59.160 --> 35:00.703
'cause that thing
wouldn't have fit.

35:00.703 --> 35:02.080
[ Both laugh ]

35:04.457 --> 35:06.334
Katherine: Okay, T.
You can read for 10 minutes.

35:06.334 --> 35:08.836
What do you guys think
of the name Emerson?

35:08.836 --> 35:12.215
Well, uh, Emerson's the name
of a great college in town.

35:12.215 --> 35:14.759
It's also the name
of the new girl in Theo's class.

35:14.759 --> 35:15.885
Ohh!

35:15.885 --> 35:17.303
Is that why
you're asking?

35:17.303 --> 35:18.805
No!

35:18.805 --> 35:20.139
I was just thinking

35:20.139 --> 35:22.558
if you and Dad
ever had another baby,

35:22.558 --> 35:24.102
you should name her
Emerson.

35:24.102 --> 35:28.648
♪♪

35:28.648 --> 35:31.234
That's a beautiful name.

35:31.234 --> 35:34.862
But I don't think Dad and I
are having any more children.

35:34.862 --> 35:36.197
Why not?

35:36.197 --> 35:39.409
♪♪

35:39.409 --> 35:41.160
Because...

35:41.160 --> 35:44.330
we have to save
all of our love for <i>you.</i>

35:44.330 --> 35:47.500
♪♪

35:47.500 --> 35:49.085
Good night.
Good night.

35:49.085 --> 35:52.964
♪♪

35:52.964 --> 35:55.216
Gina, thank you
for everything today.

35:55.216 --> 35:57.593
And not just with my folks.
W‐With me, too.

35:57.593 --> 36:00.346
And I am sorry if ‐‐

36:01.889 --> 36:05.726
I am sorry <i>that</i> the car
commercial bothered you.

36:05.726 --> 36:09.605
♪♪

36:09.605 --> 36:11.524
Rome,
I want to be married

36:11.524 --> 36:14.694
for as long
as your parents have,

36:14.694 --> 36:17.947
but I don't want
to be like them,

36:17.947 --> 36:19.866
where they don't
talk about stuff.

36:21.367 --> 36:24.537
See, I don't want you
to resent me,

36:24.537 --> 36:26.873
and I don't want
to resent <i>you.</i>

36:26.873 --> 36:28.082
You're right.

36:28.082 --> 36:32.462
♪♪

36:32.462 --> 36:33.754
So let's talk.

36:36.174 --> 36:39.385
Do you know why
this morning bothered me?

36:39.385 --> 36:42.096
Because you don't want
our personal life

36:42.096 --> 36:44.390
to play out
in a high‐end car commercial?

36:44.390 --> 36:45.808
[ Chuckles ]

36:45.808 --> 36:48.561
Well, yes.

36:48.561 --> 36:51.522
And also...

36:51.522 --> 36:56.194
I want to find a way
to give us the happy ending

36:56.194 --> 36:58.946
where we're <i>both</i> happy.

36:58.946 --> 36:59.989
Me too.

37:04.118 --> 37:05.870
So, where do we go
from here?

37:09.040 --> 37:10.541
I don't know.

37:10.541 --> 37:15.046
♪♪

37:15.046 --> 37:16.422
[ Toy squeaking ]
Ah.

37:16.422 --> 37:17.715
Hey, bud.

37:21.344 --> 37:22.762
Maggie?

37:26.891 --> 37:28.100
What?

37:28.100 --> 37:29.936
You already ate.

37:30.686 --> 37:32.021
Fine. So did I.

37:34.148 --> 37:35.191
Yep.

37:37.568 --> 37:39.070
[ Sighs ]

37:39.070 --> 37:41.364
[ "Let My Love Open the Door"
plays ]

37:41.364 --> 37:50.331
♪♪

37:50.331 --> 37:54.961
♪♪

37:54.961 --> 37:57.421
[ Sighs ]

37:57.421 --> 38:07.473
♪♪

38:07.473 --> 38:17.149
♪♪

38:17.149 --> 38:18.693
[ Beep ]

38:18.693 --> 38:22.530
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

38:22.530 --> 38:26.659
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

38:26.659 --> 38:30.037
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

38:30.037 --> 38:34.041
♪ To your heart ♪

38:34.041 --> 38:37.253
♪ To your heart ♪

38:39.171 --> 38:42.967
♪ When people keep repeating ♪

38:42.967 --> 38:44.969
[ Exhales shakily ]
♪ You'll never fall in love ♪

38:44.969 --> 38:46.804
[ Folder closes ]

38:46.804 --> 38:49.807
♪ When everybody
keeps retreating ♪

38:49.807 --> 38:51.309
[ Sniffles, sighs ]

38:51.309 --> 38:54.895
♪ You can't seem to get enough ♪

38:54.895 --> 38:58.858
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

38:58.858 --> 39:02.778
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

39:02.778 --> 39:05.781
How about...

39:05.781 --> 39:06.574
[ Keyboard clacks ]
...this one?

39:06.574 --> 39:07.742
[ Gasps ]

39:07.742 --> 39:11.120
"Our giant family
just got bigger."

39:11.120 --> 39:12.163
Perfect.

39:12.163 --> 39:13.289
[ Chuckles ]

39:13.289 --> 39:14.957
I love it.

39:14.957 --> 39:18.919
♪ When everything
feels all over ♪

39:18.919 --> 39:23.257
♪ When everybody seems unkind ♪

39:23.257 --> 39:27.345
♪ I'll give you
a four‐leaf clover ♪

39:27.345 --> 39:31.057
♪ Take all the worry
out of your mind ♪

39:31.057 --> 39:33.142
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

39:33.142 --> 39:35.645
Thanks for an amazing day,
Edward.

39:35.645 --> 39:37.063
You're welcome...Kat.

39:37.063 --> 39:37.813
[ Chuckles ]

39:39.231 --> 39:42.610
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

39:42.610 --> 39:46.656
♪ To your heart ♪

39:46.656 --> 39:50.409
♪ To your heart ♪

39:51.952 --> 39:55.706
♪ I have the only key
to your heart ♪

39:55.706 --> 39:57.875
I know this isn't something
you're supposed to say

39:57.875 --> 39:59.543
on a first date.

39:59.543 --> 40:01.837
♪ Try today,
you'll find this way ♪

40:01.837 --> 40:03.673
But I love you.

40:03.673 --> 40:06.550
♪ Come on and give me
a chance to say ♪

40:06.550 --> 40:07.718
Good night.

40:07.718 --> 40:10.471
♪ Let my love open the door ♪

40:10.471 --> 40:11.472
Good night.

40:11.472 --> 40:15.518
♪ It's all that I'm living for ♪

40:15.518 --> 40:19.730
♪ Release yourself from misery ♪

40:19.730 --> 40:23.275
♪ Only one thing's
gonna set you free ♪

40:23.275 --> 40:25.111
♪ That's my love ♪

40:27.154 --> 40:29.365
♪ That's my love ♪

40:29.365 --> 40:31.450
♪ Ooh ♪

40:31.450 --> 40:33.077
♪ That's my love ♪

40:35.246 --> 40:37.289
♪ That's my love ♪

40:40.126 --> 40:44.171
♪ When tragedy befalls you ♪

40:44.171 --> 40:47.216
♪ Don't let it bring you down ♪

40:47.216 --> 40:51.554
♪ Oh, love can cure
